<p itemprop="description">A technical writer creates comprehensive, user-focused documentation for complex digital services and technical systems. They understand user information needs, collaborate with technical teams, and produce accessible documentation that helps users successfully complete their tasks.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create comprehensive technical documentation for complex digital services</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop user-focused API documentation and developer guides</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design information architecture for documentation systems</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct user research to understand documentation needs</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with developers, designers, and product teams</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure all documentation meets accessibility and inclusion standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Test and iterate documentation based on user feedback</li>
    </ul>
</section>

